      <h1>AWG Wire Size Explained</h1>

      <p>
        <strong>AWG</strong> stands for <strong>American Wire Gauge</strong>.
        It is a standard system used in North America to describe the diameter of electrical wires.
      </p>

      <h2>How AWG Numbers Work</h2>
      <p>
        AWG numbers work in reverse:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Smaller AWG number = thicker wire</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Larger AWG number = thinner wire</strong></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Common AWG Wire Sizes</h2>
